2
00:01:30,110 --> 00:01:34,490
The Legendary Hero

3
00:01:35,070 --> 00:01:36,280
Big news!

4
00:01:36,280 --> 00:01:40,160
Beehive, the Pirate Island
New World

5
00:01:36,620 --> 00:01:38,950
Captain Koby has escaped!

6
00:01:38,950 --> 00:01:40,160
Seriously?!

7
00:01:42,870 --> 00:01:46,000
He escaped, so he's not
the commodore's prize anymore, right?!

8
00:01:46,000 --> 00:01:48,590
How much will we get if we capture him?!

9
00:01:50,340 --> 00:01:54,050
Well, we don't need to put a bounty on him!

10
00:01:54,050 --> 00:01:56,550
Cross Guild will pay it for us!

11
00:01:56,550 --> 00:01:59,430
I bought odds on him with a win ticket!

12
00:01:59,430 --> 00:02:01,390
The payout's gonna be big!

13
00:02:01,390 --> 00:02:03,390
How much will we get if we kill him?!

14
00:02:04,020 --> 00:02:05,690
Wait till you hear this!

15
00:02:07,650 --> 00:02:09,820
He's a five-star bounty!

16
00:02:09,820 --> 00:02:13,490
That means five treasure chests!
A total of 500 million berries!

17
00:02:13,490 --> 00:02:16,120
A five-star bounty?!

18
00:02:16,120 --> 00:02:18,330
Captains are usually only worth one!

19
00:02:21,160 --> 00:02:24,170
Alright! Let's hit the jackpot!

20
00:02:24,170 --> 00:02:27,040
Let the hunt begin!

21
00:02:29,340 --> 00:02:32,380
I'm feeline a tickle on
the left side of my chest.

22
00:02:32,720 --> 00:02:36,010
That's where the slaves are
held before they're sold...

23
00:02:41,720 --> 00:02:44,310
Are they breaking out?!

24
00:02:44,640 --> 00:02:46,810
The slaves escaped?!

25
00:02:47,650 --> 00:02:50,020
Can we hunt them, Pizarro?!

26
00:02:50,020 --> 00:02:51,650
Don't be stupid!

27
00:02:51,650 --> 00:02:53,490
You guys are so greedy!

28
00:02:54,030 --> 00:02:55,740
Bring them all back!

29
00:02:55,740 --> 00:02:57,200
Don't even kill Koby...

30
00:02:57,660 --> 00:02:59,280
or I'll tell Teach!

31
00:03:01,620 --> 00:03:04,080
Why is that mountain talking...?

32
00:03:04,460 --> 00:03:06,580
He knows that we're here!

33
00:03:06,580 --> 00:03:07,790
Let's hurry!

34
00:03:10,800 --> 00:03:11,750
What?

35
00:03:12,880 --> 00:03:14,720
This is it for us...

36
00:03:15,170 --> 00:03:19,720
Just run away before we slow you down.

37
00:03:19,720 --> 00:03:21,930
Don't give up hope.

38
00:03:21,930 --> 00:03:24,310
I'll lure them all away...

39
00:03:24,810 --> 00:03:28,940
so make sure everyone escapes!

40
00:03:28,940 --> 00:03:29,690
Well then...

41
00:03:30,690 --> 00:03:32,280
We'll meet again!

42
00:03:34,190 --> 00:03:35,820
Thanks!

43
00:03:38,070 --> 00:03:40,280
Thank you, Captain Koby...

44
00:03:43,330 --> 00:03:45,660
You're a saint!

45
00:03:50,630 --> 00:03:53,550
Shiryu of the Rain
Clear-Clear Fruit
Invisible Man

46
00:03:53,550 --> 00:03:58,130
You should have captured
them yourself, Pizarro.

47
00:04:02,260 --> 00:04:05,480
Like I said, Teach would be pissed.

48
00:04:04,930 --> 00:04:08,480
"Corrupt King" Avalo Pizarro
Isle-Isle Fruit
Island Man

49
00:04:08,480 --> 00:04:12,110
I just break things whenever I meowve.

50
00:04:12,110 --> 00:04:12,940
Huh?

51
00:04:16,320 --> 00:04:18,860
Mind if I take a shot?

52
00:04:18,860 --> 00:04:22,070
Vasco Shot... What are mew gonna do?

53
00:04:28,290 --> 00:04:32,040
They can't run if I burn down the town.

54
00:04:31,580 --> 00:04:35,130
"Heavy Drinker" Vasco Shot
Glug-Glug Fruit
Booze Man

55
00:04:42,720 --> 00:04:46,060
Hey, don't do that!
That would be a meowssive fire!

56
00:04:46,390 --> 00:04:48,520
Teach would be furrious!

57
00:04:48,520 --> 00:04:51,270
It's fine. Leave it to me.

58
00:04:51,770 --> 00:04:56,360
Furget it! We just finished
fixing up Rocky Port!

59
00:04:56,860 --> 00:05:00,240
Would you rather leave it to Wolf?

60
00:05:04,490 --> 00:05:05,830
Wolf?

61
00:05:05,830 --> 00:05:10,040
"Colossal Battleship" Sanjuan Wolf
Huge-Huge Fruit
Gigantification Man

62
00:05:07,700 --> 00:05:10,040
That's meowt of the question!

63
00:05:10,040 --> 00:05:13,040
Mew might as well just
destroy the whole town!

64
00:05:17,670 --> 00:05:18,760
I found him!

65
00:05:24,550 --> 00:05:26,760
Damn! I guess I can't outrun them!

66
00:05:29,270 --> 00:05:30,230
Somehow...

67
00:05:31,270 --> 00:05:36,570
I have to keep them busy until
everyone can escape to the sea!

68
00:05:38,940 --> 00:05:40,950
Koby the Hero!

69
00:05:44,870 --> 00:05:49,700
Koby the Hero, I want to turn this island...

70
00:05:51,160 --> 00:05:54,000
this Pirate Island...

71
00:05:54,380 --> 00:05:58,210
into a full-fledged nation!

72
00:05:58,210 --> 00:06:02,430
A World Government-affiliated nation!

73
00:06:03,680 --> 00:06:05,390
It'll be the Blackbeard Kingdom...

74
00:06:05,720 --> 00:06:07,760
with me as its king!

75
00:06:11,230 --> 00:06:13,190
How's that?

76
00:06:13,190 --> 00:06:15,270
Stop this nonsense.

77
00:06:15,650 --> 00:06:17,770
There's no way it would work!

78
00:06:18,190 --> 00:06:20,230
It'd be a country of criminals!

79
00:06:20,610 --> 00:06:24,610
Hey, don't step on a man's dream!

80
00:06:24,610 --> 00:06:28,620
I'll negotiate with them
using you as a bargaining chip.

81
00:06:29,910 --> 00:06:33,660
If the government or the Marines
give in to terrorists, we're all doomed!

82
00:06:34,500 --> 00:06:37,000
Anyway, you're wasting your time.

83
00:06:37,880 --> 00:06:38,920
Because...

84
00:06:39,630 --> 00:06:41,590
I'm a member of SWORD!

85
00:06:42,840 --> 00:06:44,680
SWORD?

86
00:06:44,680 --> 00:06:46,390
What the hell is that?

87
00:06:46,390 --> 00:06:47,930
Oh, I see...

88
00:06:47,930 --> 00:06:48,640
Huh?

89
00:06:48,640 --> 00:06:50,640
This isn't gonna go well.

90
00:06:50,640 --> 00:06:52,980
Give up on the trade, Teach.

91
00:07:00,650 --> 00:07:02,190
What he means...

92
00:07:02,190 --> 00:07:05,240
is that he's a Marine but also not.

93
00:07:06,530 --> 00:07:08,990
He gave up his Marine code.

94
00:07:11,200 --> 00:07:15,750
SWORD is a group of Marines that have
already submitted their resignations.

95
00:07:16,170 --> 00:07:20,340
Which means they could even fight
the Four Emperors without permission.

96
00:07:20,340 --> 00:07:24,670
They can operate however they choose
and disregard any and all orders.

97
00:07:24,670 --> 00:07:25,880
They're free agents.

98
00:07:26,380 --> 00:07:27,890
In exchange...

99
00:07:29,100 --> 00:07:32,930
the Marines are in no way
responsible for their actions...

100
00:07:33,560 --> 00:07:35,690
and can fire them anytime.

101
00:07:38,270 --> 00:07:39,650
I see!

102
00:07:40,150 --> 00:07:43,900
So there's the normal idiots who
sit around waiting for permission,

103
00:07:44,320 --> 00:07:47,740
and you guys, who charge in
without thinking twice!

104
00:07:50,200 --> 00:07:52,870
Now that I get it, I like your style!

105
00:07:54,160 --> 00:07:55,200
But...

106
00:07:55,200 --> 00:07:57,830
I'm not gonna change the plan!

107
00:07:58,420 --> 00:08:00,210
I'll do it anyway!

108
00:08:01,420 --> 00:08:03,630
Even if you're in SWORD,

109
00:08:04,340 --> 00:08:07,880
the people still call you a hero.

110
00:08:07,880 --> 00:08:11,300
I wonder if the Marines can
really afford to just abandon you.

111
00:08:12,100 --> 00:08:14,560
Let's ask the public, shall we?!

112
00:08:15,680 --> 00:08:18,730
That way the government can't just
wash their hands of this!

113
00:08:22,110 --> 00:08:24,820
Until then, lock him up!

114
00:08:26,240 --> 00:08:28,070
I can't wait!

115
00:08:28,070 --> 00:08:30,780
Don't let him escape!

116
00:08:32,530 --> 00:08:35,370
Get back here, Koby!

117
00:08:41,540 --> 00:08:42,420
Hey!

118
00:08:42,420 --> 00:08:48,720
I'll free you, so you're going to
free Master Moria from his cell.

119
00:08:49,300 --> 00:08:51,510
I may have cooperated with a pirate...

120
00:08:52,010 --> 00:08:54,390
but you gotta do what you gotta do!

121
00:09:01,940 --> 00:09:02,860
What's that?

122
00:09:12,530 --> 00:09:15,240
Three Marines spotted at the port!

123
00:09:15,740 --> 00:09:18,290
What? Marines?! No way!

124
00:09:18,910 --> 00:09:20,250
Hurry up!

125
00:09:21,290 --> 00:09:23,880
They're strong! Be careful!

126
00:09:25,670 --> 00:09:27,800
Did someone come to rescue me?

127
00:09:27,800 --> 00:09:29,130
No, no!

128
00:09:29,130 --> 00:09:30,800
How arrogant of me!

129
00:09:30,800 --> 00:09:32,010
I'm ashamed!

130
00:09:51,700 --> 00:09:52,820
Who are they?!

131
00:09:52,820 --> 00:09:54,320
Why are they so strong?!

132
00:09:54,320 --> 00:09:56,830
They're heading toward
the center of the town!

133
00:09:56,830 --> 00:09:57,790
What do they want?!

134
00:09:57,790 --> 00:10:00,200
Who cares?! Stop them!

135
00:10:07,800 --> 00:10:08,800
What?

136
00:10:08,800 --> 00:10:10,260
Guns don't work on them!

137
00:10:11,720 --> 00:10:14,050
That's as far as you go!

138
00:10:17,470 --> 00:10:19,060
He cut his head off!

139
00:10:23,560 --> 00:10:25,270
I took one down!

140
00:10:25,600 --> 00:10:26,980
That'll teach you!

141
00:10:33,570 --> 00:10:34,860
That hurt...

142
00:10:34,860 --> 00:10:35,870
What?!

143
00:10:35,870 --> 00:10:36,990
A logia?!

144
00:10:37,320 --> 00:10:38,870
What's with this guy?!

145
00:10:38,870 --> 00:10:41,160
It's like he's made of clay!

146
00:10:42,710 --> 00:10:45,080
Where are you, Koby?!

147
00:10:47,290 --> 00:10:49,040
H-Hey...

148
00:10:49,420 --> 00:10:51,800
Are those buildings moving?!

149
00:10:51,800 --> 00:10:53,550
No, stupid! Of course not!

150
00:10:53,550 --> 00:10:55,510
You drink too much!

151
00:11:02,850 --> 00:11:05,310
Go on! Be a good little boy!

152
00:11:08,440 --> 00:11:10,190
Get a move on!

153
00:11:10,190 --> 00:11:13,150
What a weird lady. Who is that?

154
00:11:13,150 --> 00:11:15,950
Come on, straighten up!

155
00:11:18,240 --> 00:11:20,580
You look pathetic!

156
00:11:20,580 --> 00:11:22,700
Come on! Come on! Come on!

157
00:11:22,700 --> 00:11:25,210
She's whipping a building...

158
00:11:26,420 --> 00:11:28,630
What is it? Staring, are we?

159
00:11:28,630 --> 00:11:30,340
What? No, I...

160
00:11:30,880 --> 00:11:33,050
S-She's a Marine?!

161
00:11:39,800 --> 00:11:43,470
Is it that rare for a pirate
to set eyes on a Marine?

